544,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

,

You should enumerate through all of the options then click on the one you want. See What is the correct way to select an <

if option.text == 'The Options I Am Looking For':

670,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

82,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

901,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

,

You should enumerate through all of the options then click on the one you want. See What is the correct way to select an <
The easiest way that I have found was to do something along the lines of:
if option.text == 'The Options I Am Looking For':
option.click() # select() in earlier versions of webdriver

250,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

995,62838668,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/62838668,How to select a option from drop down with div tag/?.selenium,

I have tried all the possible things. also, tried searching over tried different combinations and variations. I can get the element clicked which opens the dropdown. but i am not able to select an option in it. I tried with actions, sendkeys, keys.down/enter and multiple things as well. however, it didn't help. That's the only thing I am stuck on.

,

You should enumerate through all of the options then click on the one you want. See What is the correct way to select an <
The easiest way that I have found was to do something along the lines of:
if option.text == 'The Options I Am Looking For':
option.click() # select() in earlier versions of webdriver

I recently started building an audio tag editor, but now I find a problem that I can't manage to pass through.
My problem is that I don't know how to read tags in .m4a s.
I used this code to read it on mp3 s using a public external library called "
But when I tried with an .m4a just returns blank s, even using Mp4Tag and Mp4FieldKey instead of Tag and FieldKey.
Does anyone know any other external library which reads these type of audio s or just any workaround for this?
And I don't want to use MediaStore because I want the tags to be merged into the , so I can move the to another device and keep them.

,

Jaudiotagger processes mp4 and m4a exactly the same way

You are using the library to read metadata from the but it seems to me that you are assuming the already has artist and album metadata in the , but probably your second just doesnt have any metadata in it.

712,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

145,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

61,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

649,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

124,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

19,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

,

if option.text == 'The Options I Am Looking For':

229,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

103,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

922,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

,

You should enumerate through all of the options then click on the one you want. See What is the correct way to select an <
The easiest way that I have found was to do something along the lines of:
if option.text == 'The Options I Am Looking For':
option.click() # select() in earlier versions of webdriver

I recently started building an audio tag editor, but now I find a problem that I can't manage to pass through.
My problem is that I don't know how to read tags in .m4a s.
I used this code to read it on mp3 s using a public external library called "
But when I tried with an .m4a just returns blank s, even using Mp4Tag and Mp4FieldKey instead of Tag and FieldKey.
Does anyone know any other external library which reads these type of audio s or just any workaround for this?
And I don't want to use MediaStore because I want the tags to be merged into the , so I can move the to another device and keep them.

,

Jaudiotagger processes mp4 and m4a exactly the same way

You are using the library to read metadata from the but it seems to me that you are assuming the already has artist and album metadata in the , but probably your second just doesnt have any metadata in it.

,

691,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

964,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

502,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

838,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

565,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

775,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,"

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.

313,653085,https://stackoverflow.com/questions/653085,Purpose of tag library?,

What is the purpose of having tag library? Though we have the basic tags available which makes our work very simple, what is the reason to have a struts-.tld. Though we can call and use the bean easily through usebean, setProperty and getProperty tags why we have struts-bean.tld.

,

While you can do basic things like accessing bean property and using it to construct your , often you require to do much more in your pages. Struts provide a lot of well defined tags that you can use directly to construct your elements, such as your inputs fields or tables etc. And this means, you won't be dealing with elements but struts tags. Apart from providing basic elements, there are tag library that help you create more complex pages. For an e.g, with a particular tag library, you can construct neat paginated table just by providing an iterator and mapping column headers.
